history.content:
Should students who were unable to directly enroll for classes due to the bug found earlier this morning (1) remain on the waitlist or (2) keep adding / dropping the class at regular intervals to see if the system has been updated or not? It is going to be my last semester to declare so I want to guarantee my spot as much as possible.

Sorry, edit: This is with particular interest to L&S undeclared students who will be in their third year next fall trying to enroll in 61c or 70. I am NOT asking about the issues others had with upper division courses.

I ask this because while going in order of the waitlist seems the most logical, it could also be simpler to fix to have everyone just drop the course so they can re-add it after the system updates. My schedule is not very flexible so I absolutely must do everything I can.

If anyone who is going to be a third year undeclared L&S next fall who has already enrolled into cs61c or cs70, please let me (and others following this post) know!

Any help at all is appreciated!
